{
  "texts": [
    "The objectives of this paper are firstly to introduce a theoretical framework about how AI might address challenges in six key procedural areas of peer assessment.",
    "Secondly, we undertake a rapid scoping review of the literature on artificial intelligence in peer assessment with reference to these six areas.",
    "Thirdly we present a case study that illustrates the application of an AI-powered peer assessment system in five of the six areas of the framework.",
    "Fourthly the paper concludes by discussing opportunities, challenges and future research needs for the effective incorporation of AI in peer assessment, as well as the implications for practitioners.",
    "The combination of peer assessment and artificial intelligence has been explored to an extent in previous reviews."
  ]
}